The paper discusses a novel RF circuit architecture for self-interference cancellation in inband full-duplex radio transceivers. This involves signal processing techniques and hardware design for wireless communication systems, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The paper also presents actual RF measurements, which could be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Architecture (cs.AR) categories.
